"1 pint 6 fl oz (650ml) bottle. It sat on the counter for a while before I opened it so I would guess it was probably 45-47 degrees, poured into a room temperature 20oz fluted beer glass. Appearance was amazing. A little more carbonation than I expected, 2 finger white head, good retention and nice lacing. Surprisingly clear dark amber color. Smell was what I would characterize as typical IPA. Nothing outstanding or remarkable. Citrusy/piney/floural... IPA. Taste was an immediate hop forward bomb on the front of the tongue with a dry finish. Again, my reaction was that it was a good IPA, but nothing really extraordinary to separate it from the other 2 kerzillion IPA's dominating the shelf space across America. The feel was probably a bit drier than most IPA's. Overall not a bad beer at all. ""Refreshing"" would be a good one word description. I'm not sure I would run right out and buy more, but that's probably more because I'm growing extremely tired of the IPA fad."
