"I had my first bottle of this beer 2 weeks ago on vacation in OBX NC. Once I opened the bottle the beers citrus/floral came out and hit me first. Very nice poor and great legs. This beer is one of the better IPA's I have had that use cascade hops and has, like the aroma, a medium to strong citrus presence and almost completely hid its taste of alcohol. Not overly strong but definitely creeps up on you after two or three.... Again it hides its punch well. Highly recommend this beer to lovers of a more floral/citrus IPA.. Compare it as a somewhat less floral version of the Ithaca flower power. Just disappointed I can not get this beer in upstate New York!"
